SIMPLE: substituted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Substituted
<hw>Sub"stit"uted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Exchanged; put in the place of another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Containing substitutions or
replacements; having been subjected to the process of substitution, or
having some of its parts replaced; <as>as, alcohol is a
<ex>substituted</ex> water; methyl amine is a <ex>substituted</ex>
ammonia</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Substituted executor</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an
executor appointed to act in place of one removed or
resigned.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Substitution</ent>⟦br⟧
